#!/bin/python3
string_in:str = """GETS "ciao" ROT POP POP ciao POP POP EXIT 0"""
string_out:list = []
open_brackets:int = 0
closed_breackets:int = 0
alias_list:list = []
debug = True

start_header:str = """
#include <cpiatti.h>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
"""

middle_header:str = """
void code(){
init_stack();
"""

end_header:str = """
}

int main(){
    code();
    return 0;
}
"""

split_str = string_in.split(' ')
split_str = list(filter(lambda x: x != '', split_str))
if debug:
    print(split_str)
iterator = iter(split_str)

std_noarg_function = {
    "POP": "pop();",
    "GETC": "sgetc();",
    "GETI": "sgeti();",
    "STPOP": "stpop();",
    "ROT": "rot();",
    "PUT": "put();",
    "APUT": "aput();",
    "COPY": "copy();",
    "SWAP": "swap();",
    "SUB": "sub();",
    "SUM": "sum();",
    "MUL": "mul();",
    "DIV": "sdiv();",
    "REM": "rem();",
    "DROP": "drop();",
    "STPEEK": "stpeek();"
}

compare_symbol = ["==", "<=", ">=", '<', '>', "!="]

def get_arg_string(arg):
    if arg.isdigit():
        return arg
    elif arg == "SIZE":
        return "stack.size"
    elif arg == "STORE":
        return "stack.store"
    else:
        print("error value not valid: " + arg)
        exit(1)

for word in iterator:
    if word == "PUSH":
        try:
            value = next(iterator)

            value_str = get_arg_string(value)

            string_out.append(f"push({value_str});")

        except StopIteration:
            print("Error: PUSH requires a value.")
            exit(1)

    elif word == "GETS":
        try:
            string = next(iterator)
            if len(string) > 2 and string[0] == '"' and string[-1] == '"' and string.count('"') == 2:
                string_out.append(f"sgets({string});")
            else:
               print("Error: GETS requires a valid string.")
               exit(1) 
        except StopIteration:
            print("Error: GETS requires a string.") 
            exit(1)

    elif word in std_noarg_function:
        string_out.append(std_noarg_function[word])

    elif word.islower():
        #comment
        pass

    elif word == "LOOP":
        try:
            bracket = next(iterator)
            if bracket == '{':
                open_brackets += 1
                string_out.append("while (1) {")
            else:
                print("Error: LOOP missing {")
                exit(1)
        except StopIteration:
            print("Error: LOOP missing {")
            exit(1)

    elif word == "REPEAT":
        try:
            value = next(iterator)

            value_str = get_arg_string(value)

            bracket = next(iterator)
            if bracket == '{':
                open_brackets += 1
                string_out.append(f"for (size_t i = 0; i < {value_str}; i++) {{")
            else:
                print("Error: REPEAT requires a valid value.")
                exit(1)
        except StopIteration:
            print("Error: REPEAT requires a value.")
            exit(1)

    elif word == "EXIT":
        try:
            value = next(iterator)

            value_str = get_arg_string(value)

            if value.isdigit():
                string_out.append(f"deint_stack();\nexit({value_str});")
            else:
                print("Error: EXIT requires a valid value.")
                exit(1)
        except StopIteration:
            print("Error: EXIT requires a value.")
            exit(1)

    elif word == "IF":
        try:
            arg1 = next(iterator)
            comparator = next(iterator)
            arg2 = next(iterator)
            open_brackets += 1

            arg1_str = get_arg_string(arg1)
            arg2_str = get_arg_string(arg2)

            if comparator in compare_symbol:
                string_out.append(f"if ({arg1_str} {comparator} {arg2_str}) {{")
            else:
                print("Error: IF requires a valid comparator.")
                exit(1)

        except StopIteration:
            print("Error: IF requires three arguments.")
            exit(1)

    elif word == "ELSE":
        try:
            bracket = next(iterator)
            open_brackets += 1
            if bracket == '{':
                string_out.append("else {")
            else:
                print("Error: ELSE missing {")
                exit(1)
        except StopIteration:
            print("Error: ELSE missing {")
            exit(1)

    elif word == '}':
        closed_breackets += 1
        string_out.append('}')

    else:
        print(f"error synthax {word}")
        exit(1)

if open_brackets != closed_breackets:
    print("error brackets miss match")
    exit(1)

if debug:
    for i in string_out:
        print(i)